{"word":"G3870 - παρακαλέω - parakaléō - par-ak-al-eh'-o - Beseech","slug":"G3870","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">παρακαλέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>parakaléō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>par-ak-al-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beseech"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03C1;&#x03B1;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - parakaleo&#x0304;</b> - <i>par-ak-al-eh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G3844\">G3844</a> and <a href=\"#/G2564\">G2564</a>; to <i>call near</i>, that is, <i>invite</i>, <i>invoke</i> (by <i>imploration</i>, <i>hortation</i> or <i>consolation</i>): - beseech, call for, (be of good) comfort, desire, (give) exhort (-ation), intreat, pray."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3874\">G3874</a>, <a href=\"#/G3875\">G3875</a>, <a href=\"#/G870\">G870</a>"}]}